data.meta_description:
175 likes, 2 comments - akbarthegreat03 on May 3, 2019: "Akbar's tomb is the tomb of the  Mughal  emperor,  Akbar  and an important  Mughal architectural masterpiece. It was built in 1605–1613 and is situated in 119 acres of grounds in  Sikandra, a sub of Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India! 
Akbar planned the tomb and selected a suitable site for it. After his death, Akbar's son Jahangircompleted the construction in 1613.
